ry, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘tendril’ or ‘creeper’, often used in metaphors describing the slender curvature of eyebrows, arms, hair, swords, lightning, and women's bodies."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Marcy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."],"variants":[{"name":"Marsha","meanings":["Phonetic spelling of   Marcia  , associated particularly with the American film star  Marsha Hunt  (  b. 1917 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Agnes Marcy Styelinge was born in 1530, in Colchester, Essex, England, United Kingdom, her father, Thomas Halsnoth Harsnett, was 16 and her mother, Agnes Holsnoth, was 13. She had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Sir William Halsnoth. She died on 22 June 1620, in her hometown, at the age of 90."},"et":{"1530–22 Jun 1620":"1530–22. juuni 1620","1530–1620":"1530–1620","1552–Female":"1552–Surnud","1554–1639":"1554–1639","1561–1631":"1561–1631","1573–Female":"1573–Surnud","1515–1600":"1515–1600","1517–1569":"1517–1569","24 June 1569":"24. juuni 1569","1561":"1561","August 1573":"august 1573","22 Jun 1620":"22. juuni 1620","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","1554":"1554","1631":"1631","1620":"1620","Bef. 1600":"enne 1600","1530":"1530","1552":"1552","1573":"1573","22 June 1620":"22. juuni 1620","1639":"1639","1517":"1517","1515":"1515","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Colchester , Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1530–22 Jun 1620":"1530–22. kesäkuuta 1620","1530–1620":"1530–1620","1552–Female":"1552–Kuollut","1554–1639":"1554–1639","1561–1631":"1561–1631","1573–Female":"1573–Kuollut","1515–1600":"1515–1600","1517–1569":"1517–1569","24 June 1569":"24. kesäkuuta 1569","1561":"1561","August 1573":"elokuu 1573","22 Jun 1620":"22. kesäkuuta 1620","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","1554":"1554","1631":"1631","1620":"1620","Bef. 1600":"ennen vuotta 1600","1530":"1530","1552":"1552","1573":"1573","22 June 1620":"22. kesäkuuta 1620","1639":"1639","1517":"1517","1515":"1515","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Colchester , Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England"},"fr":{"1530–22 Jun 1620":"1530–22 juin 1620","1530–1620":"1530–1620","1552–Female":"1552–Décédée","1554–1639":"1554–1639","1561–1631":"1561–1631","1573–Female":"1573–Décédée","1515–1600":"1515–1600","1517–1569":"1517–1569","24 June 1569":"24 juin 1569","